trans-unit.source: Specifies that a property or method is viewable in an editor.
This class cannot be inherited.
<xref:System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableAttribute> is a hint to a designer indicating whether a property or method is to be displayed.
You can use this type in a visual designer or text editor to determine what is visible to the user.
For example, the IntelliSense engine in [!INCLUDE[vsprvs](~/includes/vsprvs-md.md)] uses this attribute to determine whether to show a property or method.

In [!INCLUDE[csprcs](~/includes/csprcs-md.md)], you can control when advanced properties appear in IntelliSense and the Properties Window with the **Hide Advanced Members** setting under **Tools | Options | Text Editor | C#**.
The corresponding <xref:System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableState> is <xref:System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableState.Advanced>.
In [!INCLUDE[csprcs](~/includes/csprcs-md.md)], <xref:System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableAttribute> does not suppress members from a class in the same assembly.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableAttribute"></xref> class with <xref href="System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableAttribute.State"></xref> set to the default state.
The default for this property is <xref:System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableState?displayProperty=fullName>.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableAttribute"></xref> class with an <xref href="System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableState"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableState"></xref> to set <xref href="System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableAttribute.State"></xref> to.
Returns whether the value of the given object is equal to the current <xref href="System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableAttribute"></xref>.
The object to test the value equality of.
`true` if the value of the given object is equal to that of the current; otherwise, `false`.
Returns the hash code for this instance.
A 32-bit signed integer hash code.
Gets the browsable state of the property or method.
The default for this property is <xref:System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableState?displayProperty=fullName>.
An <xref href="System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableState"></xref> that is the browsable state of the property or method.
